The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Good Morning

 Hello It's Monday, June 18, 2007

 Book launch

 Settle for More: The Why, How and When of Meditation by Shriram Panchu, will be released at Oxford Bookstore, 7pm. Followed by an interactive session: Litigate or Mediate?

 Interface

 The Music Room presents Birth of a Song, an interactive music session, at Seagull Bookstore, 6.30pm.

 Lecture

 Lecture on India in Global Science: Are we ready for it? at the Asiatic Society, 4pm. 

 Stagecraft

 A quartet of short plays by Frank D. Glory, produced by Stagecraft, at Starmark, 7.30pm.

 Raindrops and Verses, an evening of cultural events, at Dignity Foundation, 70 Babubagan Lane, 5pm.

 Monsoon

 Monsoon Magic, an exhibition of cotton dress materials, at Soumyas Creation, 57/9 Ballygunge Circular Road, 10.30am.

 Art watch

 Summer Show, an exhibition of art works by various artists from across India, at CIMA Gallery, 3pm to 7pm.

 Intimate Thoughts, Pristine Fables, works by women artists from Santiniketan, at Akar Prakar, 2pm to 7pm.

 Confronting Globalisation, an exhibition of art works by various artists, at Mon Art Gallerie, 11am to 7pm.

 Tapestry and Serigraph, an exhibition by S.H. Raza, will open at Gallery K2, 35 Lansdowne Terrace, 6pm.

 A show of watercolours by Milanendu Mondal, at Domus Art Gallery, 11am to 6pm.




